ATRAPP transcriptomics

October 11, 2018

This is an R Markdown Notebook. When you execute code within the notebook, the results appear beneath the code. Try executing this chunk by clicking the Run button within the chunk or by placing your cursor inside it and pressing Cmd+Shift+Enter.

SAMSA2:standalone metatranscriptome analysis pipeline

• samsa2 repo
• samsa2


 

RefSeq

• Species + protein name • 27G, 68M sequences

Subseed

• SEED Subsystems: hierarchical functional activity (4 levels) • 7.6G, 2.9M sequences

Data

• Lake Champlain metatranscriptomes (2 X 100bp Illumina HiSeq) • 3 sampling site: PRM (15 samples), St1 (27 samples), St2 (23 samples) • 130 fastq samples (79G of fastq.gz data)

Running the pipeline

• Compute Canada Cedar • 48 CPUs, ~15hr X 3 sampling sites • I ran the pipeline seperately for each sampling site

Examining the output

Merging

pe_assembly = read.table("results/summary_stats/pe_assembly",stringsAsFactors = F)
pe_assembly[,7] = sub("%","",pe_assembly[,7],fixed=T)
pe_assembly[,7] = sub("(","",pe_assembly[,7],fixed=T)
pe_assembly[,7] = sub(")","",pe_assembly[,7],fixed=T)
hist(as.numeric(pe_assembly[,7]),xlab = "% merged",main= "merging PE")
mean(as.numeric(pe_assembly[,7]))

Trimmomatic

trimmed = read.table("results/summary_stats/trimmed",stringsAsFactors = F)
trimmed[,9] = sub("%","",trimmed[,9],fixed=T)
trimmed[,9] = sub("(","",trimmed[,9],fixed=T)
trimmed[,9] = sub(")","",trimmed[,9],fixed=T)
hist(as.numeric(trimmed[,9]),xlab = "% trimmed",main= "Trimmomatic")
mean(as.numeric(trimmed[,9]))

Ribosomes

ribosomes = read.table("results/summary_stats/ribosomes",stringsAsFactors = F)
ribosomes[,9] = sub("%","",ribosomes[,9],fixed=T)

ribosomes[,9] = sub(")","",ribosomes[,9],fixed=T)

Annotations

refseq = read.table("results/summary_stats/refseq",stringsAsFactors = F)
subsys = read.table("results/summary_stats/subsys",stringsAsFactors = F)
hist(refseq[,1],xlab="nb reads annotated",main = "Annotation REFSEQ")

hist(subsys[,1],xlab="nb reads annotated",main = "Annotation SUBSYS")

#Total Number of sequences (~20k sequences / megabyte of fastq.gz)
nb_seq = 79*1000*20000 
#What fraction of sequences are annotated (remember that here a merged sequence is composed of the 2 PEs)
#refseq
signif(sum(refseq[,1])/(nb_seq/2)*100,4)
[1] 11.51
#subsys

• We can ID the Dolichospermum bloom nicely • What is going in the St1 samples on Sept 15th? • Inediibacterium massiliense and Blautia massiliensis are human fecal bacteria…

I. massiliense

• ALL Inediibacterium massiliense 20160915_St1 sequences match to a single hypothetical (i.e predicted) protein. • e-values ~e-20 (because sequences are small + %identity ~90%)

I. massiliense genome BLAST

• Download I. massiliense genome. • BLAST all sequences. • Sequences BLAST to a single region of ~150bp.

B. massiliensis

• ALL Inediibacterium massiliense 20160915_St1 sequences match to a single hypothetical (i.e predicted) protein. • e-values ~e-20 (because sequences are small + %identity ~90%)

B. massiliensis genome BLAST

• Download I. massiliense genome. • BLAST all sequences. • Sequences BLAST to several region of the genome.
